The source shows Florence with a humid subtropical climate. It meets Köppen's minimum precipitation threshold limit of 30 millimetres (1.2 in) (or 40 millimetres (1.6 in) under Köppen-Geiger), for this designation.
Correction: Casablanca also has a Mediterranean climate because it also receives enough annual precipitation to avoid Köppen's BSh (semi-arid climate) classification.

Readded Los Angeles because (like Athens) receives just enough annual precipitation to avoid Köppen's BSh (semi-arid climate) classification, unlike San Diego, Alexandria, Casablanca or Nicosia which are far too dry.
